  "prompt": "What is the minimum level of mathematical proficiency required to graduate from West Point?",
  "response": "To graduate from the United States Military Academy at West Point, cadets are required to have a strong foundation in mathematics. The core curriculum includes several mandatory mathematics courses. Typically, cadets are expected to complete courses in calculus, probability and statistics, and possibly linear algebra and differential equations. While the exact course requirements may vary slightly over time and depend on a cadet's chosen major, a solid proficiency in these areas is generally necessary to meet the graduation requirements. The curriculum is designed to ensure cadets have the necessary analytical and problem-solving skills critical for military leadership.",
